DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(93)90121-K
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440769390121K
AB  - This paper presents lower bounds on the asymptotic variance of estimators for various semiparametric models of discrete choice. No greatest lower bound exists for some partial observability models, where the dependent variable consists of a single binary indicator. No regular estimators exist for these models even though the models are identified. For other partial observability models the greatest lower bound is finite and coincides with the asymptotic efficiency of certain index estimators. However, some examples show that index estimators do not achieve the efficiency bound in general when choices are fully observed.
